  "prompt": "Where do I download Quora for Windows 10?",
  "response": "Quora does not provide a dedicated desktop application for Windows 10. However, you can access Quora using a web browser on your Windows 10 computer. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n1. Open your preferred web browser (such as Google Chrome, Microsoft Edge, Firefox, etc.).\n2. Navigate to the Quora website by typing `www.quora.com` into the address bar and hitting Enter.\n3. If you already have an account, log in using your credentials. If you don\u2019t have an account, you can sign up for free.\n\nFor a more app-like experience, you can create a shortcut to Quora on your desktop:\n\n1. Open Quora in your web browser.\n2. Click on the browser menu (three dots in the upper right corner for Chrome, or similar for other browsers).\n3. Select \u201cMore tools\u201d and then \u201cCreate shortcut\u2026\u201d or \u201cInstall Quora\u201d depending on the browser.\n4. Follow the prompts to create a desktop shortcut.\n\nThis will allow you to access Quora easily from your desktop, mimicking an app-like experience.",
